BMI Calculator


name = input ("Enter your name: ")
Enter your name: Ani
weight = input("Enter your weight in pounds: ")
Enter your weight in pounds: 140
height = input ("Enter you height in inches: ")
Enter you height in inches: 64

weight = int(weight)
height = int(height)

BMI = weight/ (height**2)*703

print (str(name) + ", your BMI is: " + str(BMI))
​
if BMI < 18.5:
    print("You are Underweight")
elif BMI >= 18.5 and BMI <= 24.9:
    print("You are Normal weight")
elif BMI >= 25 and BMI <= 29.9:
    print("You are overweight")
elif BMI >= 30 and BMI <= 34.9:
    print("You are Obese")
elif BMI >= 35 and BMI <= 39.9:
    print("You are Severely Obese")
elif BMI >= 40:
    print("You are Morbidly Obese")
else:
    print("please enter your weight in pounds and your height in inches")
​
Ani, your BMI is: 24.0283203125
You are Normal weight
